women's liberation). Only after finding applications did he realize
some were volunteers and others "no shows" — this led to interest in
explaining why some made it to Mississippi and others didn't, plus
longer-term impact of going/not-going on two groups.
- **Impossible for them to withdraw** — McAdam noted significance of
organizational ties: not that they make withdrawal impossible, but
that they insure applicant will likely receive support for link
between salient identity (Christian) and participation in summer
project. Strong subjective identification with particular identity,
reinforced by organizational ties, especially likely encourages
participation.
- **"Getting together there without you"** — Tom Mathews and Roy
